{"title": "History of the Norwegian People, Volume 1", "description": "A detailed and exhaustive history of the Norwegian People, written in two volumes. The author, Knut Gjerset, was born in Western Norway in 1865 and immigrated to Chippewa County, Minnesota, in the US with his parents in 1871 and his brother Oluf later got elected to public office there. He received a B.A. in Literature from the University of Minnesota, and also studied at John's Hopkins University from 1895-1896, and the University of Heidelberg, where he was awarded a PhD, from 1896-1898. This first volume deals with the Norwegian History from the earliest times, to the early 14th century and covers topics such as: Prehistoric Norway and iron and Bronze age cultures in the area, the Viking era, The Christianization of Norway and some related information on Iceland, the Faroe Islands, Shetland/Orkney Islands, etc., Early kings of Norway, Norway in the Crusades, and foreign policy reformations at the beginning of the Late Middle Ages. - Summary by \u00c6rik Bj\u00f8rnsson", "duration": 59575, "language": "English", "authors": [{"id": "12350", "name": "Knut Gjerset"}], "coverArt": "https://archive.org/download/historynorwegianpeople1_1712_librivox/history_norwegian_people_1712.jpg", "copyright_year": "1915", "genres": ["Antiquity", "Middle Ages/Middle History"], "supporters": [{"role": "Read by", "name": "\u00c6rik Bj\u00f8rnsson"}, {"role": "Book Coordinator", "name": "\u00c6rik Bj\u00f8rnsson"}, {"role": "Meta Coordinator", "name": "TriciaG"}, {"role": "Proof Listener", "name": "DaveC"}], "sections": [{"section": 0, "title": "Preface", "readers": [11190], "path": "http://www.archive.org/download/historynorwegianpeople1_1712_librivox/historyofnorwegianpeoplevol1_00_gjerset_64kb.mp3", "duration": 177}, {"section": 1, "title": "The Country and Its Resources", "readers": [11190], "path": "http://www.archive.org/download/historynorwegianpeople1_1712_librivox/historyofnorwegianpeoplevol1_01_gjerset_64k